  4. Built-in Algorithms
  
  Ano to: Pre-made ML algorithms na ready to use — XGBoost, Linear Learner, Image
  Classification, etc.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang instant mix — hindi mo na kailangang gumawa ng recipe from
  scratch. May ready-made na, i-mix mo lang sa data mo.
  
  5. Model Registry
  
  Ano to: Version control para sa ML models — parang Git pero para sa trained models. May
  approval workflow pa.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang filing cabinet ng mga recipe versions mo — v1, v2, v3. May stamp
  pa kung "approved for production" na.
  
  6. Endpoints (Real-time Inference)
  
  Ano to: Pag gusto mong gamitin yung trained model, ide-deploy mo as endpoint — parang
  API na pwede tawagan anytime.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang Jollibee drive-thru — order ka, sagot agad. Milliseconds lang.
  
  7. Batch Transform
  
  Ano to: Para sa bulk processing — hindi real-time, pero kaya mag-process ng millions of
  records.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang catering service — hindi instant, pero kaya mag-serve ng 500
  people in one go.
  
  8. Serverless Inference
  
  Ano to: Endpoint na nag-o-on lang pag may request. Pag walang tao, naka-off. Cost
  savings.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang food truck — nandyan lang pag may customer. Pag wala, naka-park
  lang. Hindi ka nagbabayad ng renta 24/7.
  
  9. Async Inference
  
  Ano to: Para sa malalaking requests na matagal i-process. Mag-submit ka, tapos
  "tatawagan ka namin pag ready na."
  Pinoy analogy: Parang online order na "we'll text you when ready" — for heavy
  workloads.
  
  10. SageMaker Pipelines
  
  Ano to: CI/CD pero para sa ML. Automated workflow from data prep → training →
  evaluation → deployment.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang assembly line sa factory — automated na yung process from raw
  materials hanggang finished product.
  
  11. SageMaker Data Wrangler
  
  Ano to: Visual tool para mag-clean at mag-prepare ng data — no code needed.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang rice winnower (bilao) — nililinis yung bigas bago iluto.
  Tinatanggal yung dumi at hindi kailangan.
  
  12. SageMaker Feature Store
  
  Ano to: Central storage ng processed features (data columns) na pwedeng i-reuse across
  multiple models.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang palengke na pre-cut vegetables — hindi mo na kailangang mag-chop
  every time. Ready to cook na.
  
  13. SageMaker Experiments
  
  Ano to: Tracking tool para sa lahat ng experiments mo — anong parameters ginamit, anong
  results nakuha.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang lab notebook ng scientist — nire-record lahat ng ginawa para alam
  mo kung alin ang best recipe.
  
  14. SageMaker Debugger
  
  Ano to: Real-time monitoring ng training job — nakikita mo kung may problema habang
  nag-t-train pa.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang CCTV sa kusina — nakikita mo agad kung nasusunog na yung niluluto
  mo bago pa masira lahat.
  
  15. SageMaker Model Monitor
  
  Ano to: Monitors deployed models for data drift at quality degradation over time.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang quality inspector sa factory — chine-check kung consistent pa
  yung output. Pag bumaba ang quality, mag-a-alarm.
  
  16. SageMaker Clarify
  
  Ano to: Detects bias sa data at models. Explains kung bakit ganun ang prediction ng
  model.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang auditor — chine-check kung fair yung decisions ng AI. Walang
  favoritism.
  
  17. SageMaker Ground Truth
  
  Ano to: Data labeling service — pwede human labelers o automated. Para ma-tag yung
  training data mo.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang nag-hire ka ng tao para mag-sort ng photos — "ito aso, ito pusa,
  ito kotse." Para matuto yung AI.
  
  18. SageMaker Canvas (No-Code ML)
  
  Ano to: Point-and-click ML — walang coding needed. Upload data, pick target, train
  model.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang Canva pero para sa AI — drag and drop lang, may ML model ka na.
  Para sa non-developers.
  
  19. SageMaker JumpStart
  
  Ano to: Pre-trained models at solutions na ready to deploy — one-click lang.
  Pinoy analogy: Parang IKEA furniture — pre-built na, i-assemble mo lang konti, tapos
  usable na agad.
  
  20. SageMaker Edge Manager
  
  Ano to: Deploy at manage ML models sa edge devices (IoT, cameras, etc.)
  Pinoy analogy: Parang nag-deploy ka ng security guard sa bawat branch — hindi na
  kailangan tumawag sa main office para mag-decide. Kaya na nila mag-isa.
  
  21. Spot Training
  
  Ano to: Gamitin ang spare AWS capacity para mag-train — hanggang 90% savings sa cost!
  Pinoy analogy: Parang standby ticket sa eroplano — mas mura, pero pwedeng ma-interrupt.
  Okay lang kasi SageMaker auto-resume naman.
  
